    <h1>Voices of the Land</h1>
    <p><strong>Voices of the Land</strong> is a community-driven digital tool designed to help Indigenous communities record, preserve, and share their unique dialects and languages. Each word or phrase is submitted by community members and verified by Elders before being made public in the digital dictionary.</p>

    <h2>How It Works</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>ðŸŒ¿ <strong>Community members</strong> submit words or phrases in Cree.</li>
      <li>ðŸª¶ <strong>Elders</strong> review and verify each submission for accuracy and cultural permission.</li>
      <li>ðŸŒŽ Once verified, words become part of the <a href="dictionary.html">Public Dictionary</a>.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Start Here</h2>
